Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.27,0:00:02.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Hi it's me, Tim Dodd the Everyday Astronaut.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.29,0:00:06.57,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}We're less than a week away from this year's Starship update from Elon Musk,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.57,0:00:08.27,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and before the party gets started,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.27,0:00:11.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}we're already catching some major changes happening before our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.51,0:00:15.05,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That's because as we speak SpaceX is building the Mark 1 Starship prototype,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.08,0:00:19.70,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}right there in Boca Chica where the presentation will be held on September 28th.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.70,0:00:23.28,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And of course, because it's being built out in a field in public,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.28,0:00:25.66,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}we're seeing some major updates to the hardware.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.66,0:00:27.15,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The most obvious change is the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.18,0:00:32.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that the Starship has only two finney flappy air-brakey things now instead of three,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.18,0:00:35.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and the previous version touted just a year ago at the Dear Moon event
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.36,0:00:39.69,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}showed Starship sporting three fins that were also its landing legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.69,0:00:41.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So now that we're seeing it only has two,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.65,0:00:44.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the question has come up, and it's come up a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.97,0:00:47.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Why, why just two?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.30,0:00:51.45,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So today, we're gonna do a really quick rundown on why two might be better than three,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.45,0:00:54.44,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}show you some potential problems that three fins had,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.44,0:01:00.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and then we'll show you exactly how they'll control the re-entry and landing with just two rear fins.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.67,0:01:01.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.07,0:01:14.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- Okay, first things first.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.34,0:01:17.77,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I think it'd be fun to do a quick rundown here on this fun little bit of engineering
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.77,0:01:19.53,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}while we get ready for the event on the 28th,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.53,0:01:22.83,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so, when it gets revealed, we can be like, "Ah, yeah."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.83,0:01:26.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And since I've been way too busy now for over two months,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.52,0:01:30.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}working on what's become literally a documentary on the aerospike engine,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.68,0:01:33.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I figured I'd better crank out a nice easy video here in the meantime.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.91,0:01:35.25,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay, so now before we get going,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.25,0:01:38.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I wanted to remind you these are not wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.62,0:01:40.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They are really just giant air brakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.64,0:01:44.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or body flaps, as Elon once called them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.44,0:01:48.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They are perpendicular to the airstream and not parallel,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.72,0:01:51.66,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but we'll call them fins or flaps interchangeably in this video.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.66,0:01:54.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And another note. We're gonna use Kerbal Space Program here in this video.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.97,0:01:58.23,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And if you're triggered by a game, settle down, settle down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.23,0:02:02.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}We're gonna use Kerbal to illustrate some of the problems and demonstrate some of the solutions,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.67,0:02:08.45,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but we're doing this knowing this isn't an engineering tool for validations or argument sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.45,0:02:11.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Regardless, it's still a great demonstrator of the basic physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.64,0:02:14.83,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it definitely helps visualize some of the challenges involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.83,0:02:19.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay, so let's start off with the obvious reason of why there's now two fins instead of three.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.59,0:02:21.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Wait, according to Elon Musk,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.71,0:02:24.61,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}"Current analysis, which I'm not fully bought into,"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.61,0:02:28.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}"suggests that two rear fins with separate airframe-mounted legs will be lighter,"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.97,0:02:31.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}"so this is the plan for Mark 1 and Mark 2."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.47,0:02:35.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So it sounds like there may be some internal debate here on what's lighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.96,0:02:39.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and for now, two fins seems to have won out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.30,0:02:44.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But part of me thinks that Elon really loved the old-school look of the three fins at the rear.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.40,0:02:48.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I know he mentioned how it reminded him of Tintin's rocket many times,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.11,0:02:50.77,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and considering how much he loves aesthetics,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.77,0:02:52.99,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}this might actually be kind of true.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.99,0:02:55.10,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- I think it looks beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.10,0:02:57.57,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And I love the Tintin rocket design,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.57,0:03:00.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so I kind of wanted to bias it towards that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.13,0:03:02.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}- And I'm a little torn up on this one actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.04,0:03:06.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because I thought it was super cool that the landing legs were also the control surfaces.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.62,0:03:10.14,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But then again, there was that third leg that didn't articulate at all
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.16,0:03:12.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and would've had a lot of additional dead weight,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.91,0:03:13.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and not to mention,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.86,0:03:16.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}making your control surfaces also handle the weight
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.70,0:03:21.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and impacted the entire ship would've likely been rather difficult to engineer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.40,0:03:23.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, I'm not saying it couldn't be done in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.84,0:03:26.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it might not be something that they update to later on,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.98,0:03:30.99,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but for now, the easiest path forward for these first prototypes,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.99,0:03:33.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}if they separate the landing legs from the fins,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.19,0:03:35.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it might have simplified things quite a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.26,0:03:40.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Not to mention, say you had a rough landing on Mars and broke a landing gear,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.52,0:03:44.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}at least it's not integrated into your primary control surface
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.35,0:03:47.44,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that helps you survive re-entering Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.44,0:03:52.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean, that's unlikely, but having the two systems separate might not be a bad thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.73,0:03:54.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}especially as they develop the vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.59,0:03:59.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And after all, don't forget, these first prototypes are really just technology demonstrators.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.20,0:04:04.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They're flying science experiments that are built as inexpensively and quickly as possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.41,0:04:06.88,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}to start shaking out some of these new technologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.88,0:04:09.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Nothing on Starship is set in stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.62,0:04:13.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean, look at how much the Falcon 9 evolved in such a short timeframe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.84,0:04:16.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Starship is taking that concept up another notch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.37,0:04:22.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So, if the easiest path forward for now is landing legs on the body and the flaps separate,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.41,0:04:24.32,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}sweet, yeah, get it going.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.32,0:04:25.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At last year's Dear Moon event,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.76,0:04:28.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it stood out to me that Elon said a few times
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.06,0:04:33.46,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}how the third leg is only a leg and it's not a rear stabilizer of any kind,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.46,0:04:38.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and mostly because on re-entry that fin is entirely in the wake of the vehicle
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.13,0:04:40.50,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it doesn't even touch the airstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.50,0:04:45.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Later on, if it does prove to actually be lighter to integrate the landing legs onto the flaps,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.59,0:04:50.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}nothing's going to stop SpaceX from evolving Starship to do exactly that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.43,0:04:52.74,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But in the meantime, I actually think
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.74,0:04:54.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that the aerodynamics team at SpaceX
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.60,0:04:59.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}was likely begging engineering to reconsider three fins for a few reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.97,0:05:02.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, here's where we're going to get into speculation land for a little second,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.96,0:05:06.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but I've always been questioning how three would've worked,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.01,0:05:08.27,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because of some basic physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.27,0:05:11.74,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5u,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}About exactly your ago I did a video about the belly-flop maneuver,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.74,0:05:16.22,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5u,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and in order to help me get it to work well I had to keep the fins tucked in on ascent,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.22,0:05:20.05,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5u,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and I needed to keep them behind the center of mass on descent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.05,0:05:21.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Here, let me show you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.48,0:05:24.28,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The general rule of thumb for anything flying is,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.28,0:05:28.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}you want your center of pressure or lift behind your center of mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.55,0:05:31.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Otherwise, if the vehicle moves away from its heading at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.51,0:05:34.63,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the surfaces will induce lift or torque on the vehicle,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.63,0:05:37.57,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and since it's in front, it'll become a feedback loop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.57,0:05:39.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Say it pulls up just a little,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.26,0:05:42.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that's going to change the angle of attack on the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.37,0:05:44.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which will make it pitch up a little more,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.29,0:05:46.74,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which will change the angle of attack on the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.74,0:05:48.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which will make it want to pull up a little more,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.56,0:05:50.53,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which will change the angle of attack on the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.53,0:05:52.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which will make it wanna, et cetera, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.31,0:05:53.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}until you lose control,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.59,0:05:58.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that surface will want to flip around to the back where it belongs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.68,0:05:59.81,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That's because, in the back,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.81,0:06:04.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}those forces actually do the exact opposite thing and work to stability's advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.71,0:06:07.23,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}When a craft starts to pitch away from its heading,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.23,0:06:09.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the fins apply torque to recenter the craft.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.85,0:06:13.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The further away from your heading you pitch the more torque it applies,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.40,0:06:16.50,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which makes it very inherently stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.50,0:06:22.05,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This principle applies to Starship during three different phases, ascent, re-entry and landing,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.05,0:06:24.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it does so in three very different ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.95,0:06:25.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That's why,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.29,0:06:28.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}when we started seeing renderings and animations of the three-fin Starship
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.87,0:06:31.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}ascending on the super-heavy booster,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.35,0:06:34.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}my eyes got a little wide and I got a little worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.11,0:06:37.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}When I saw that, I thought about throwing a dart backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.31,0:06:40.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's probably not gonna fly backwards very long,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.00,0:06:43.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it's probably gonna flip right over and orient itself so the fins are in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.91,0:06:45.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, that's not to say it can't be done,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.49,0:06:48.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because the engines have an awful lot of control authority with their gimbal,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.93,0:06:51.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and they can help maintain proper orientation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.49,0:06:54.99,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But in general, it's much, much more difficult to fly
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.99,0:06:59.02,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with large aero surfaces that far out in front of your center of mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.02,0:07:03.54,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Luckily, computers are really good at managing crazy aerodynamic properties,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.54,0:07:08.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is why all modern fighter jets are inherently unstable and are fly-by-wire,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.62,0:07:12.15,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}where computer actually interprets the input from the pilot
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.15,0:07:16.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and moves whatever surfaces necessary to move the aircraft as the pilot intended.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.55,0:07:25.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay, so why would two be better than three on ascent?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.43,0:07:28.05,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Won't two still be an issue?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.05,0:07:31.09,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Besides the fact that there's less fins in the first place,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.09,0:07:34.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}there's something two can do that three can't really do easily,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.91,0:07:37.60,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that's get tucked in away from the airstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.60,0:07:40.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}While on ascent, a pair of fins can easily tuck in against their airframe
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.10,0:07:44.06,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and mostly negate their aerodynamic properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.06,0:07:46.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Both the top and bottom fins will do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.72,0:07:51.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Whereas three fins, especially when one was an immobile landing leg only,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.92,0:07:54.80,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}can't really tuck in out of the airstream entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.80,0:07:57.70,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean, sure, they could've tucked two in and left the third one out
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.70,0:08:01.22,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and kept that more in the wake of the vehicle during its gravity turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.22,0:08:04.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but it's still just not the most stable configuration.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.48,0:08:05.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay, but forget ascent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.93,0:08:09.15,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm sure they can do that no problem either way if they had to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.15,0:08:14.16,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The bigger challenge is actually with the descent of Starship, with three versus two fins.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.16,0:08:18.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And again, this has everything to do with tucking the fins in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.00,0:08:20.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Let's actually watch the real physics simulation
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.58,0:08:23.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that Elon showed at last year's Dear Moon presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.49,0:08:29.75,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You'll see the vehicle does the belly-first to tail-down flip at only about 1.5 kilometers in altitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.75,0:08:32.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}while still traveling at mach one for landing on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.97,0:08:34.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now notice, during this landing phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.89,0:08:39.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the rear fins are tucked in all the way until the very last second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.49,0:08:45.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But even so, the vehicle has one giant fin fully eating the wind stream in front of the vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.26,0:08:48.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Any movement away from the vehicle's heading will induce a lot of torque.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.79,0:08:50.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And again, the gimbals on the Raptors
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.54,0:08:54.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and the attitude control thrusters can offset all of this torque
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.59,0:08:56.39,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and hopefully maintain stability,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.39,0:09:03.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but if you have the option of eliminating something that's going to actively try and make your vehicle lose control,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.97,0:09:05.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it might not be a bad idea to change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.87,0:09:07.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And Elon did go on to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.01,0:09:13.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}"Stability is controlled by very rapid movement of rear and forward fins during entry and landing,"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.04,0:09:16.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}"as well as ACS thrusters," or attitude control thrusters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.78,0:09:21.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}"The smaller leeward fin would simply be used as a leg."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.84,0:09:25.16,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But I think he's mainly talking about re-entry,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.16,0:09:27.86,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because during the actual landing portion,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.86,0:09:32.45,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the legs and upper fins can only articulate on their dihedral axis.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.45,0:09:35.83,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, if these fins had the ability to also act like canards,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.83,0:09:41.15,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which would be able to produce two axes of control through the x-axis of the rocket,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.15,0:09:43.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I can see where the statement would be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.03,0:09:46.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But during the final tail-down landing portion,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.00,0:09:48.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they are essentially passive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.19,0:09:50.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Notice, with just the two fins on the bottom,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.29,0:09:52.50,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}again, just like on ascent,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.50,0:09:57.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}we can tuck them in against the fuselage and mostly negate their aerodynamic effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.73,0:10:02.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Not to mention, there aren't any portion of these new fins that are sticking out below the engines,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.30,0:10:06.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which would put them in front of the airstream of the vehicle as it descends,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.01,0:10:08.17,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which again is a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.17,0:10:11.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The other problem with the three landing legs is a little more complicated,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.51,0:10:13.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but I'll bet the aerodynamics team had a pretty great time
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.98,0:10:16.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}going over the properties of the three-legged re-entry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.85,0:10:21.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}When re-entering, the vehicle will be completely belly-flopping, and that is,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.18,0:10:24.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}coming in broadside with its belly facing the airstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.95,0:10:26.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Well, hold on actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.19,0:10:27.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It'll mostly belly-flop.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.87,0:10:29.81,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But it sounds like, according to Elon Musk,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.81,0:10:33.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}"It does actually generate lift in hypersonic regime,"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.04,0:10:35.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}"which is important to limit peak heating."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.82,0:10:38.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In other words, it could probably pitch down a little bit,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.07,0:10:41.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which would allow the body to create a little additional lift,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.40,0:10:45.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which can also limit peak heating and make sure it doesn't ever get too hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.20,0:10:49.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}With three legs, they're attached at a 120 degrees apart from each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.00,0:10:53.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which puts the two fins that articulate awfully close to the center of mass of the rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.98,0:10:57.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, this isn't necessarily a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.08,0:11:00.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In fact, a traditional capsule shape intentionally has
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.12,0:11:03.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}a center of pressure in front of the center of mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.01,0:11:05.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This is known as blunt body dynamics,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.20,0:11:08.75,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and in 1952, H. Julian Allen of NACA,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.75,0:11:11.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}now NASA's Ames Aeronautical Lab,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.21,0:11:15.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}discovered a capsule was most stable and dissipated the most heat
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.68,0:11:18.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}when it had a blunt surface facing the wind stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.37,0:11:21.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So, perhaps the fins could function in this manner,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.18,0:11:25.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but considering how much they actually need to move throughout re-entry,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.00,0:11:29.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I could see it again being less stable than having those fins behind the center of mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.43,0:11:34.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I even wonder if they do end up going with integrating the legs back onto the fins someday,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.30,0:11:38.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}if they'll have a retractable third leg that would be in the front of the vehicle,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.37,0:11:39.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so facing windward,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.84,0:11:44.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and let the other two fins remain behind the center of mass for better passive stability.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.78,0:11:47.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So this is another time we're having just two fins,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.04,0:11:49.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}when partially retracted through the re-entry,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.72,0:11:53.14,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}would have a better, more passively stable configuration.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.14,0:11:57.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But again, I'm sure they really cool ways to deal with some of these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.13,0:11:58.66,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But I'm thinking they actually made
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.67,0:12:03.06,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}a significantly more stable vehicle by only having two fins in the rear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.39,0:12:06.81,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}If we see them tucked in on ascent and tucked in on landing,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.81,0:12:10.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that kind of proves that this is indeed advantageous.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.08,0:12:13.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay, so that's a quick overview of why I think two is better than three.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.47,0:12:14.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So let's have some fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.68,0:12:15.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and I'm gonna show you just
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.68,0:12:22.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}how exactly you can control all three axes of control with just two upper fins and two lower fins.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.20,0:12:25.02,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, this method of control hasn't actually changed at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.02,0:12:30.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because that third fin on the back was really completely passive and out of the wind stream,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.11,0:12:34.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so everything we talk about here is the same way it would've worked with three fins in the back too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.82,0:12:37.99,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's actually a really cool method of control,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.99,0:12:40.17,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I've never really seen anything like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.17,0:12:42.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Remember, these flaps are perpendicular to the wind stream
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.31,0:12:47.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and not parallel like the wings or ailerons of an airplane.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.11,0:12:51.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The only thing we can do is increase or decrease the amount of drag each one produces.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.65,0:12:56.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Remember, a plane typically uses a change in lift or deflection to induce pitch, yaw, and roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.92,0:13:01.17,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Starship will essentially use drag brakes to control its pitch, yaw and roll,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.17,0:13:03.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and most aircraft do not do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.76,0:13:06.75,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}My favorite example of this is the B-2 Stealth Bomber,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.75,0:13:08.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which doesn't have a tail stabilizer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.89,0:13:11.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So, in order to induce yaw,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.00,0:13:13.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it actually opens up what's called a split aileron,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.68,0:13:16.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which can induce drag on one wing or the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.76,0:13:18.80,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which then controls the jet's yaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.80,0:13:19.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Here's how this works.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.92,0:13:23.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, we're still gonna consider the cockpit our frame of reference for pitch, yaw, and roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.90,0:13:28.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}To induce pitch, the top and bottom fins can move opposite each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.35,0:13:30.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}One extends more while the other retracts,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.67,0:13:33.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which can help pitch the nose up or push it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.40,0:13:36.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}To induce roll, the left and right flaps can move opposite each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.89,0:13:39.63,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Extend one side more than the other and the vehicle will roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.63,0:13:41.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But you can even induce yaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.43,0:13:44.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}For this, we move opposite corners of each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.19,0:13:48.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Top left and bottom right can move opposite of the top right and bottom left.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.13,0:13:51.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This will induce yaw as it belly-flops through the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.11,0:13:56.33,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And this is exactly why Elon keeps saying this vehicle is more like a skydiver than an airplane.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.33,0:14:01.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}A skydiver needs to use their limbs to control themselves in a very similar manner,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.08,0:14:03.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}something I once found out I'm awful at.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.93,0:14:06.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's a lot harder than it looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.93,0:14:11.05,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Every tiny bit of movement I make creates a lot of torque,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.05,0:14:13.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}thanks to the grids on my grid fin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.34,0:14:14.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So, throughout re-entry,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.52,0:14:19.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the computer will be continually adjusting the flaps to maintain orientation and a stable configuration,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.72,0:14:22.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but they can also adjust their total drag coefficiency
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.96,0:14:25.80,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}to help perfectly nail their downrange distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.80,0:14:29.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And don't forget, the vehicle can also use attitude control thrusters throughout re-entry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.82,0:14:32.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But with that being a limited quantity,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.18,0:14:34.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the more work the flaps can do the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.82,0:14:37.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, it's gonna maintain this orientation as long as it can,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.37,0:14:42.66,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because that belly-flop does an awesome job of slowing it down without using any propellant,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.66,0:14:45.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so they really wanna do that flip as late as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.59,0:14:47.60,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}After all, as soon as it goes tail down,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.60,0:14:50.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it's actually a lot more aerodynamic and will fall a lot quicker,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.84,0:14:53.46,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so the engines actually have a lot more work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.46,0:14:55.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Once the vehicle's ready to do its flip,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.26,0:14:58.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they're going to tuck the rear fins in and extend the upper ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.76,0:15:00.66,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Then they'll light up three of its Raptor engines,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.66,0:15:02.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and alongside with the ACS,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.68,0:15:07.33,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they're going to reorient the rocket so it basically ends up landing kind of like a Falcon 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.60,0:15:22.17,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And then, when the timing is just right,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.17,0:15:24.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they're going to extend those landing legs,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.62,0:15:33.86,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}throttle the engines just perfectly and hopefully make a perfect, perfect touchdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.86,0:15:36.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Yes, there we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.37,0:15:38.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay, that's the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.92,0:15:46.06,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-5t,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That's what I'm talkin' about, right there. Holy cow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.06,0:15:48.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, that will be something to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.07,0:15:54.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean, come on, I can't help but laugh about how ho-hum Falcon 9 landings have become already.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.12,0:15:58.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}God, we really do have the attention span of a bunch of five-year-olds, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.58,0:15:59.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And in case you're wondering,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.62,0:16:02.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}yes, I do have the craft file link in the description.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.29,0:16:07.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's all stock, but it does utilize Kerbal Breaking Ground DLC for those robotics.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.36,0:16:08.33,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So, to summarize,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.72,0:16:14.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I truly don't think aerodynamic considerations was the primary reason we're now seeing two fins on Starship,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.84,0:16:18.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but I can't help but think it's inherently more stable now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.41,0:16:22.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And when dealing with something that's as big as a skyscraper falling out of the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.33,0:16:24.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with hundreds of tons of explosive propellant on board,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.75,0:16:28.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it's probably a good idea to have physics on your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.89,0:16:31.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It sounds like the primary reason is weight and simplicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.95,0:16:34.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And just again a friendly reminder,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.67,0:16:37.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I don't think I know better than anyone on the subject matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.79,0:16:41.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm literally the last person you wanna have working on your spaceship.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.93,0:16:47.05,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But teaching some of these fun principles and applying them to new designs is super fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.05,0:16:49.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And knowing just how much Elon Musk cares for aesthetics,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.76,0:16:55.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I still think his love for the retro styling was a big factor in having three fins,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.29,0:16:57.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because quite frankly, it did look really cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.82,0:16:59.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.03,0:17:04.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Do you like the two fin version, or are you gonna miss the old retro-throwback three fin version?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.36,0:17:06.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Do you think they'll stick with the two fin for a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.47,0:17:11.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or do you think we'll see them go back to three after these Mark 1 and Mark 2 prototypes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.07,0:17:14.69,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Do you think they'll tuck in on ascent and portions of descent as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.69,0:17:17.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Let me know what you think and let me know if you have any other questions about re-entry,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.93,0:17:20.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}landing burn, Raptor engine, Starship,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.37,0:17:23.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or just rockets in general, in the comments below.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.01,0:17:24.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And be sure and stick around,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.29,0:17:27.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because not only am I going down to Boca Chica for the Starship presentation,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.76,0:17:31.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm also going to do a video about why Starship doesn't have an abort system.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.96,0:17:32.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.85,0:17:38.42,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'll hopefully have my long long long video about aerospike engines done soon as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.42,0:17:40.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I promise, it's coming along great,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.00,0:17:43.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and hopefully, you learn as much as I did making it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.03,0:17:48.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I of course also a huge thank you to my Patreon supporters for helping me make all content possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.41,0:17:49.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}including traveling around all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.98,0:17:53.14,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}trying to get as much content out there for you guys as I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.14,0:17:57.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's been a crazy time lately and you guys are definitely helping me stay sane.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.52,0:17:59.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}If you wanna join our exclusive subreddit,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.36,0:18:02.53,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}our exclusive Discord or gain access to exclusive live streams,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.53,0:18:07.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or even give your input to scripts and catch errors on videos before they come out,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.41,0:18:13.10,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}please consider becoming a Patreon member by going to patreon.com/EverydayAstronaut.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.10,0:18:13.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.93,0:18:16.22,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And while you're online, be sure and check out my web store,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.22,0:18:19.63,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is getting way cooler every single day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.63,0:18:20.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Seriously, you have to check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.93,0:18:22.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}We have lots of awesome stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.68,0:18:24.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And if you see something in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.37,0:18:27.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}you better get it while it's in there because we do runs of shirts now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.68,0:18:29.50,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So, that means the quality can go up,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.50,0:18:33.14,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}we can do custom things like have tags and lots of other cool things.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.14,0:18:35.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So if you see something, grab it while it's in stock,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.31,0:18:38.42,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}otherwise it might not be coming back and it might be too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.42,0:18:41.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And don't forget, if you work in the aerospace industry,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.20,0:18:44.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}you can click on the link in the description of any apparel item,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.36,0:18:46.50,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and you can actually take 25% off
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.50,0:18:51.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}as my thank you to you for doing awesome things and for helping inspire me to do what I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.40,0:18:54.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So head on over to EverydayAstronaut.com/shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.07,0:18:55.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Thanks, everybody. That's gonna do it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.87,0:18:57.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm Tim Dodd, the Everyday Astronaut,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.91,0:19:01.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}bringing space down to earth for everyday people.
